---
alwaysApply: true
---
# Coding

ts: strict. no `any`. no `as` casts without comment. infer where obvious.
naming:
  components: PascalCase
  fns/vars/hooks: camelCase
  constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE
  types/interfaces: PascalCase, no I-prefix

files: one component per file. filename = component name. hooks: use prefix.
imports: alias @/ = src/. no relative ../../.
fns: pure where possible. keep short. single responsibility. early returns.
components: arrow function notation. one component = one file
no: any, ts-ignore, console.log, magic numbers, nested ternaries, default exports for utils.
exports: named for utils/hooks/types. default for components/pages.
errors: always handle. never silent catch. user-facing or rethrow.
formatting: prettier default config. no manual formatting.
docs:
  src/lib/ and src/hooks/:
    add TSDoc to exported functions and non-trivial helpers:
      description: 1-2 lines. state intent/constraints.
      params: document each param.
      returns: document return value.